01fcf5f-60c8-4890-9e8f-6086b297b39b","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf06076-job`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Compute HMAC Signature","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"6dadc6d6-0031-e308-6216-e1e1918de41a","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute HMAC Signature\n\nComputes the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw payload to verify the sender's signature before trusting the data.\n\nNext: Signature Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"9c125043-a627-b4d7-e922-652b44289919","name":"Note: Compute HMAC Signature"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Signature Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.computedSignature === $json.headers['x-signature']`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Map to Canonical Schema · ②→ Reject (HTTP 401)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"bf374b85-c2b7-0e84-9a50-af5508bb0c16","name":"Note: Signature Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reject (HTTP 401)\n\nSends the HTTP 401 response back to the caller — keep this fast; heavy work happens after/async.","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,1000],"id":"9586cfa5-67f1-cdec-15b6-7b5ee97a1aaf","name":"Note: Reject (HTTP 401)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Map to Canonical Schema\n\nShapes the item: writes `jobId`, `kind`, `payload`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Route by Event Kind","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"b8a91e4b-90e0-fda2-f207-db36c843eb7d","name":"Note: Map to Canonical Schema"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Route by Event Kind\n\nRoutes each item to one of 4 lanes: payment, refund, dispute + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Handle 'payment' → Airtable · ②→ Handle 'refund' → Forward API · ③→ Handle 'dispute' → Forward API · ④→ Log Unrecognized Kind","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"02e3644b-4284-b0ac-a305-6f0de363e9bd","name":"Note: Route by Event Kind"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'payment' → Airtable\n\nairtable — `upsert` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,250],"id":"13d576ec-de4f-bac4-78af-71976c043b2b","name":"Note: Handle 'payment' → Airtable"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'refund' → Forward API\n\nPOST https://api.example.com/v1/jobs — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,760],"id":"ff1ffb33-aad0-da29-65d2-6f0f111f6847","name":"Note: Handle 'refund' → Forward API"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'dispute' → Forward API\n\nPOST https://api.example.com/v1/jobs — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,1270],"id":"236dcc49-5d4e-2927-8a41-572289305767","name":"Note: Handle 'dispute' → Forward API"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Log Unrecognized Kind\n\nairtable — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,1780],"id":"8d41ba69-ee2b-03d2-a584-9306020d0064","name":"Note: Log Unrecognized Kind"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Consolidate Handling\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Respond with Outcome","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,520],"id":"70c98067-32f2-56eb-60e8-e3db00a05131","name":"Note: Consolidate Handling"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Respond with Outcome\n\nSends the HTTP 200 response back to the caller — keep this fast; heavy work happens after/async.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"2951072b-571f-b84d-83e3-227895313046","name":"Note: Respond with Outcome"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nnotion — `getAll` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"b3636ec5-af83-9705-3993-99aef48a88d6","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"9fd1312c-9a47-594c-6aff-221d6ec2e843","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"5895efa9-3948-76e8-ae29-614709e37548","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"2d008270-7451-3a7e-a9e2-7ba7ba4f4a35","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"2c978433-6220-1196-91bf-884fe60a58ab","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"eb132131-85cf-aa96-e8b6-4cd57bb469d1","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"3f5e4535-611c-9086-084c-b2e8a7c726b3","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"b2f384dd-4284-083d-d724-395b1c23c2d1","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"4e95302b-b441-3bf4-3cd9-76eaa84e412e","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"e52a4512-5333-e431-6251-39db20459f73","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per job (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"cfab84e4-99c9-2cc9-4403-b4fbc699abc2","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"871f2c32-4838-1892-2e7e-843eed76c93a","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 100 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"c19abbe4-401a-b599-404b-15ad33dbbf8f","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"891fe43e-dbb8-c581-f5cf-5e4e8339e1d4","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"de49a49e-a5c0-f505-7c42-a8a375660741","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"aea4abb8-7fcc-197e-436a-d250ddf0b12b","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"1d75b3f6-930e-4621-0ecd-8d1d1da9b275","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,520],"id":"ef9afe79-d395-ccd6-1ea0-59bcc9454d17","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,1540],"id":"43933257-c8b6-8546-c405-a26ccf4cc0da","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,1540],"id":"1aef8a60-734d-72fa-71f0-9c5401d5f786","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,1540],"id":"549e5b21-e8d2-54a6-f896-3b0ef454eec6","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Ingest API callbacks with Airtable automatically\n\n**Pattern:** Webhook Pipeline · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nIngest API callbacks with Airtable automatically. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual process orchestration is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Compute HMAC Signature → Signature Valid? → Map to Canonical Schema → Route by Event Kind → Handle 'payment' → Airtable → Consolidate Handling → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to webhook pipeline without manual effort\n- Anyone automating process orchestration in productivity\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Responds in seconds\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Airtable PAT; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"0e112f52-ffa3-ab7e-39e0-52c6d08b19b3","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"cd502e65-3738-6ae5-0c26-31e747d14853","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable, and the HMAC signature is verified before any processing. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"3e089af0-c3d3-aefc-dfb1-8456b04c694a","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"d9445bd8-9f37-94b4-a300-8e8201105fdd","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your process orchestration process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-290],"id":"a48bd960-96b8-9499-f052-5cdb5f08f73f","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute HMAC Signature","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute HMAC Signature":{"main":[[{"node":"Signature Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Signature Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Map to Canonical Schema","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Reject (HTTP 401)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Map to Canonical Schema":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Event Kind","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Event Kind":{"main":[[{"node":"Handle 'payment' → Airtable","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Handle 'refund' → Forward API","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Handle 'dispute' → Forward API","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Log Unrecognized Kind","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'payment' → Airtable":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'refund' → Forward API":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'dispute' → Forward API":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Log Unrecognized Kind":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":3}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Consolidate Handling":{"main":[[{"node":"Respond with Outcome","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Respond with Outcome":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"67906b26-3fd3-4c48-aeaf-4786a6360980","id":"FDX06076"}